==English==

===Etymology===
From a Germanic imitative base ''*kox-'' (unattested in Old English, but probably present as ''*cohhian''; compare [[cohhetan]] ‘shout’).  Cognate with Dutch [[kuchen]] ‘cough’, German [[keuchen]] ‘pant’.

